                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.52/77.</note>
                <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Embassy of Spain</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-12-12">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 12, 1913</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My dear Mr. Counselor</hi>: The news which I had the honour
                    to communicate to you this morning, verbally and by note, regarding the menace
                    of Francisco Villa to Spaniards residing in Chihuahua, has been confirmed by a
                    telegram which I have just received from the Spanish Minister in Mexico, who
                    informs me that 400 Spaniards have been ordered to leave the State of Chihuahua
                    in ten days’ time and <pb facs="1008" n="904" xml:id="pg_904"/> to abandon their
                    properties, under pain of death, if these orders are not complied with.</p>
                <p>I need not dwell upon the gravity of the situation and I trust that the United
                    States Government will spare no effort to ensure the protection of the lives and
                    properties of my compatriots.</p>
                <p>Believe me [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Juan Riaño</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
